## Variety Origin
Jiyu 303 was developed through a hybrid combination using Kexi 8 as the maternal parent and He 99-756 as the paternal parent in 2003. It was selected and bred over multiple years using the pedigree method.

## Characteristics
- Growth period: 119 days from emergence to maturity, belonging to a medium-early maturing variety
- Plant architecture: Semi-finite podding habit, plant height of approximately 85.0 cm, main stem type with 1-2 branches
- Plant and seed traits: Brown pods at maturity, pointed leaves, purple flowers, brown hairs; round seeds with yellow glossy seed coat and yellow hilum, 100-seed weight of 18.3 grams
- Disease performance: Moderately susceptible to cyst nematode race 3 via artificial fungus inoculation; resistant to mosaic virus, gray spot disease, and downy mildew under field natural induction tests
- Seed nutrient content: Crude protein 40.86%, crude fat 20.0%
